ng (whipping) cream","20 g icing sugar","1 banana, cut into thin slices"]}],"id":"r277484","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-AvYEBBc4kL4\/XZWqMYjQEkI\/AAAAAAAAfUc\/rHqdiN65Bx8fltQuqJgxyreW9271Vie7QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FI5AOZAtju3Zvger.png","title":"Banoffee tartlets","publishedAt":"2018-05-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.6 g","fat":"25.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"30.9 g","calories":"1537.2 kJ \/ 36.6 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, round cookie cutter (10 cm), rolling pin, small loose-bottom tartlet tins (6 cm), plastic wrap, baking paper, pie weights, rice or dried beans, fork, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Any remainder pastry can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days or in the freezer for up to 2 weeks.","To save time, start making the toffee sauce while pastry cases are baking."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 45m","12 portions"]}